properties.description: This is the string of data delimited by a defind delimiter

properties.name: String Data Input
properties.description: concatenated string data which is delimited by any character data to be converted into csv rows of the defined number by the ValuesPerRow Input variable

properties.name: CsvDataRow
properties.description: This variable holds the data after if was converted into rows and converted into CSV

properties.name: Delimeter
properties.description: Define the delimeter in the input string to be converted into rows

properties.name: ValuesPerRow
properties.description: Total number of values to be put in table per row

Precondition: Concatenated string with any delimiter, Defined delimiter, Number of rows requested to be in the CSV
Post Condition: Output of a csv string which divides the number of values in the concatenated string input parameter to an equal number of rows

Note: Atomic will fail with error if the string elements cannot be divided evenly by the number of requested rows.
